  "prompt": "Which banks cooperate with Costa Rica gambling websites?",
  "response": "I don't have access to current databases or lists of banks that cooperate with gambling websites, including those in Costa Rica. Banking relationships with gambling sites can be complex and are often subject to local regulations, industry changes, and privacy concerns. Many banks may choose not to openly disclose partnerships with gambling operations due to regulatory scrutiny or internal policies.\n\nIf you're looking into gambling-related banking options in Costa Rica, you might want to consider:\n\n1. **Local Regulations**: Understand the legal framework governing gambling in Costa Rica to know what is permissible.\n   \n2. **Direct Inquiries**: Contact the gambling websites or platforms directly to see which payment methods they support.\n\n3. **Payment Processors**: Look into commonly used payment processors that work in the gambling industry, such as e-wallets or prepaid cards. These can act as intermediaries between banks and gambling sites.\n\n4. **Financial Advice**: Consider seeking advice from a financial consultant or legal expert familiar with gambling operations in Costa Rica.\n\nAlways ensure compliance with local laws and international banking regulations when engaging in online gaming transactions.",
